Enterprise Root
---------------
scripts which need root access but are called with lower privileges. The Enterprise Root Pattern provides a Solution for this issue by calling the script itself as sudo.
<code>
if [ ! `id -u` -eq "0" ] 
then
  echo "not root, trying sudo"
  exec sudo "$0" "$@"
fi
</script>
